  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. The hemolysis power-law model form is grounded in the peer-reviewed methodology described in the literature reference cited via referencesIdentifier. Decision: Accepted based on demonstrated compliance with all required credibility levels after targeted model improvements.",
